theorem interior_closure_idempotent {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))) =
      interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
  -- First, show the left-hand side is contained in the right-hand side.
  have h₁ :
      interior (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))))
        ⊆ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
    -- `closure` is monotone, and taking `interior` preserves inclusions.
    have hSub :
        closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))
          ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
      exact closure_mono
        (interior_subset : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X))
    exact interior_mono hSub
  -- Next, show the reverse inclusion.
  have h₂ :
      interior (closure (A : Set X))
        ⊆ interior (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))) := by
    -- `interior (closure A)` is open and lies inside its own closure.
    have hOpen : IsOpen (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := isOpen_interior
    have hIncl :
        (interior (closure (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆
          closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
      exact subset_closure
    -- The maximality property of `interior` upgrades the inclusion.
    exact interior_maximal hIncl hOpen
  -- Combine the two inclusions to obtain equality.
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem closure_interior_eq_self_of_closed_of_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hClosed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (hP1 : Topology.P1 (A : Set X)) :
    closure (interior (A : Set X)) = A := by
  simpa using
    ((Topology.P1_closed_iff_closure_interior_eq (A := A) hClosed).1 hP1)
